Cuero ISD Health Services will be conducting hearing and vision and A/N checks on PK, KG,1st, 3rd, 5th and 7th grade students on the following dates:

JCF- September 29,30 and Oct. 1
Hunt- October 13 and October 14
CJHS- October 5 and 7

If you have a child/children in grade levels not listed above and have a concern about their hearing or vision, please speak with your child's teacher or campus nurse and screening arrangements can be made.

Please note Best Practices for Vision, Hearing and Spinal Screening During the COVID-19 Pandemic form DSHS will be followed.

ANY STUDENT DISPLAYING ANY SIGNS OF ILLNESS WILL BE RESCHEDULED AT A LATER DATE.

We received confirmation of a lab confirmed case of COVID-19 on August 31st. The last day the infected child accessed JCF campus was 8/27. There is also one confirmed close contact was with their siblings they are quarantining at this time. We have no other confirmed close contacts at this time. Any area the infected student may have accessed will be thoroughly cleaned and disinfected before the start of school for Tuesday. ATTENTION CUERO HIGH SCHOOL PARENTS/GUARDIANS:

We received confirmation of a lab confirmed case of COVID-19 on August 28th. The last day the infected child accessed high school campus was 8/27. We have confirmed this child got sick at home, other family members have symptoms and are quarantining. There is also one confirmed close contact. They had close contact outside of school and they are being tested and quarantining. We have no other confirmed close contacts at this time. Any area the infected student may have accessed will be thoroughly cleaned and disinfected before the start of school for Monday. The student did not ride the bus so no transportation contact occurred. Please limit communications about this matter to the COVID-19 response team at covidteam@cueroisd.org. We will take responsibility for notifying individuals who may have been exposed. This process will ensure the student's personal and medical information is kept confidential.

For The Children,
Micah A. Dyer, Ed.D.
Superintendent
Cuero ISD

Our teachers will be turning in a log for the previous week and your child’s attendance will be updated. post_text:
REMINDER 100% OF CISD STUDENTS ELIGIBLE FOR THIS

The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer, or P-EBT, application is open till June 30th. You should have received a school email or letter with more information on how to apply for these food benefits. P-EBT is for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and for children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. You could receive up to $285 per child on a P-EBT card to purchase food at stores. If you have not received P-EBT information from your school, please contact 833-613-6220. Visit hhs.texas.gov/PEBT for more information.

EVERY CUERO ISD STUDENT IS ELIGIBLE. Please see attached login instruction.

*The application will ask for the student ID number. DHS suggests that you use the social security number in that field instead of the student ID number.

post_text:
The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer, or P-EBT, application is open till June 30th. You should have received a school email or letter with more information on how to apply for these food benefits. P-EBT is for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and for children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. You could receive up to $285 per child on a P-EBT card to purchase food at stores. If you have not received P-EBT information from your school, please contact 833-613-6220. Visit hhs.texas.gov/PEBT for more information.

EVERY CUERO ISD STUDENT IS ELIGIBLE. Please see attached login instruction.

*The application will ask for the student ID number. DHS suggests that you use the social security number in that field instead of the student ID number.

Graduating Seniors: This order form is for any who are interested in purchasing a video of the Graduation Ceremony on Friday night. Please pay attention to the payment options listed on the order form. CHS will NOT be taking any money/order forms for it. post_text:
GRADUATION

We were going to come out earlier this week and announce Graduation would happen on May 22nd. After receiving directives from the Governor’s office and TEA we had to push the date back.

TENTATIVELY
Friday June 5th 7:30 p.m. @ Gobbler Stadium
We will have limited access/seating, social distancing protocols will be in place, and specific rules will be posted for all participants.

Please be patient we will post rules at a later date.

IF WE ARE TOLD NO AGAIN
We have plans available for a drive-up graduation or one at a time ceremony. Currently indoor ceremonies are not allowed for more than 5 people.

WAIT AND SEE
Again, be patient we get new mandates sometimes daily as soon as we can we will put out more information.

God Bless and Be Safe.

For The Children,
Micah A. Dyer, Ed.D.
Superintendent
Cuero ISD

post_text:
CHS SENIORS:

Each year our top ten students give a bell to a Cuero ISD educator who was impactful on their life or educational career. In addition to the 10 students, we let one student give an eleventh bell.

The student is chosen based on the essay they write to their chosen recipient.

Any senior who is not a member of the top ten may submit an essay. These essays need to include the student’s name and the recipient of the bell on the top of the essay. The essays need to be written describing how this educator impacted your life (write as if you are reading it to them as this is what you will do at the ceremony) and do not include the recipient’s name. Completed essays should be emailed to bbullock@cueroisd.org and pfleener@cueroisd.org BY WED, MAY 13, 2020

Seniors, if you came to pick up your cap and gown on Monday and did not receive a yard sign, please come and pick up the yard sign on Wednesday between 10:00 AM and 11:00 AM

Attention Seniors: the Caps & Gowns are in! Please be sure to pick them up from the school, on any of the following days:
Monday, May 4th
Tuesday, May 5th
Wednesday, May 6th
Pick up times are from 10:00-11:00 am, each day.

Please pull up through the horseshoe in front of the school. Do NOT exit your vehicle. Someone will hand your order to you, through the window. Also, if you’ve ordered anything else besides the Caps & Gowns (frames, invitations, etc.) they are not in at this time. We will get those to you at a later date. Caps & Gowns only.

If you have NOT ordered a Cap & Gown, and still need one, we will have extras that you may purchase. Price is $60.00 for the Cap, Gown, and Tassel package. *First come, First serve* (Cash/Check only). Make checks payable to Balfour. If using cash, please have exact change!

We look forward to seeing you all!

post_text: CHS students have been adjusting to a new way of learning with the online/packet assignments. CHS staff recognizes the challenges this will present, so through May 15, 2020, all Dual Credit, Dual Enrollment and/or AP students will have the option of taking these classes Pass/Fail instead of a number grade. The student will be responsible for informing their teacher(s) of their decision. Due to the grading decision of excluding Spring semester grades, this will not affect the seniors rank and/or GPA.

Dear Gobbler Family,

If you watched Governor Abbott today he announced schools are closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. We will continue with the current online education and packets for the remainder of the school year until May 21st. Report cards will be mailed after that date. Criteria for grading, grade reports, and class ranking will be released soon.

We are currently working out plans and details for graduation.

From now until May 21st meals will be served and delivered on Monday and Thursday only between 10am-12pm. Summer feeding details will be out before May 21st.

God Bless and be safe.

For the children,

Micah A. Dyer, Ed.D.
Superintendent
Cuero ISD

We will extend school closures through May the 4th.

Students need to continue to work online or through packets. Continue to access staff/teachers through the directory listed on the school website. God Bless and Be Safe.

For The Children,

Micah A. Dyer, Ed.D.

post_text:
Dear Gobbler Family,

Thank you again for being patient with us as we gather information and make decisions.

Updates and clarifications

*We are currently on Spring break. No students are at school. If they are there it is of their own choice. Using the track, playing ball with friends, etc. Schools are not open.
*Today is a big day in the decision making process, we are going to get alot of information on school closures and current emergency management procedures.
*I will be in meetings with state, regional, and local decision makers most of the day.
*We will explore the logistics of educating, feeding, and providing services for students and staff for the next several months.
*Friday is still the day will release information/ plans regarding next steps.

Once again thank you for your patience we get new information hourly and I will try to answer questions as quickly as possible.

For the Children,

Micah A. Dyer, Ed.D.
Superintendent
Cuero ISD

Cuero Junior High School
College & Career Fair
Monday, March 9, 2020
8 a.m. to 12:35 p.m.

All students, including athletes, will report to CJH the morning of Monday, March 9. Breakfast carts will be set up at 7:30 a.m. in multiple locations. Students are encouraged to wear college shirts and jeans. Students do NOT need to bring backpacks. The Kona Ice truck will be onsite with snow cones for sale for $3, $4, and $5 during the outdoor rotations. All students will have lunch from 12:35 - 1:05 p.m. There will be a "When Sean Speaks" guest speaker and presentation in the CHS new gym from 1:30-2:30 p.m. for all secondary students followed by regular 8th period.

post_text:
Cuero ISD would like to encourage parents of students in grades 9th through 12th to attend the Parent Program for Aim For Success, Inc. The program will be held at the Cuero High School Library on Monday, March 9th from 7:30 AM-8:30 AM.

The Aim For Success program “XTREME” will be presented later that day to all high school students and will address teen pregnancies and the escalating STD epidemic.
A form will be sent home with your child prior to the event. If you do not want your child to attend this program, please be sure to fill it out and send it back with them to school. You only need to send it back if you DO NOT want them to attend. Otherwise, they will hear the program on March 9th. Please join us for this meaningful program if at all possible.

post_text:
Attention Hunt Elementary Families:
We have some exciting things in store next week, so please make sure your child attends school throughout the entire day if possible. Please refrain from making appointments that are not required as we want our students to experience the following educational opportunities:

Monday, March 2: Sensational SkyDome Planetarium & 4th Grade Writing Camp; Cozy Up to a Good Book (2nd and 3rd Grade students have the option to wear pajamas to school within guidelines)

Tuesday, March 3: Sensational SkyDome Planetarium and 5th Grade Reading and Math Camps (3rd Grade will eat lunch at 12:35-1:05 p.m. and 5th Grade will eat lunch at 11:25-11:55 a.m. on this day to accommodate these special events); Cat in the Hat Day (2nd and 3rd Grade students have the option to wear stripes and/or Cat in the Hat attire within guidelines)

Wednesday, March 4: College Day—optional to wear a college shirt of choice OR optional to dress in "rodeo" attire as part of Round Up Wednesday

Thank you for supporting your child’s education!

Cuero ISD will host the 2020 Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo Judged Student Art Show.

The judged art will be displayed at the Chisholm Trail Museum starting on January 25th through the 29th.

The schedule for the display is as follows:
Saturday January 25th - 10am-4:30pm (Official Open House)
Sunday January 26th - Noon-4pm
Monday-Wednesday 27th-29th - 10am-4:30pm
The display is free and open to the public during these times. Enjoy the student art and get the full experience of the beautiful Chisholm Trail Museum.

post_text: Substitute Training: The Cuero ISD will hold substitute training on Monday, Jan. 6, from 1 p.m. - 4 p.m. in the Cuero High School library and computer lab located at 920 East Broadway, Cuero. This training will provide individuals wishing to work in the classroom, cafeteria, or driving a bus with information necessary for success. All new substitutes must attend this training. New applicants need to bring a copy of their social security card, driver’s license, and transcript or diploma to the training as well. Applicants that have not completed an application with the Cuero ISD, need to go to www.cueroisd.org. Any questions regarding this training, contact Jessica Hernandez at 361-275-1914.

41 Super Spellers from Hunt Elementary competed today in our Annual Hunt Elementary Spelling Bee! Congratulations to ALL who participated! Jewelee Arriaga and Cheyanne Harris are the 2019 Hunt Elementary Co-Champions and will represent Hunt in the DeWitt County Spelling Bee. Aaron Maldonado is Hunt's Runner-Up. Thank YOU to Amy Arroyo, Melissa McClellan and Charla Jones for coordinating the event. A special Thank YOU to Mary K Rabe, Patsy Kainer and Sandra Tate for serving as judges, to Kim Clutter for serving as our Orator and to Oscar Ray for filming. Awesome Job!

CUERO HIGH SCHOOL:

The Cuero Independent School District recently experienced a network security incident that affected certain computer lab, library, and other systems at the high school. We immediately took measures to contain the incident and launched an investigation with the assistance of a forensic firm. We also notified state and federal law enforcement.

We want to reassure students and parents that critical school operations are functional and that school remains in session. We are working diligently to bring the affected systems back online. We understand the importance of protecting the information of our students, faculty, staff, and community. As we work to complete the investigation of this incident, we will also look for opportunities to further enhance our existing security measures. We appreciate your patience as we work through this incident.
